The paper describes a conversational speech recognition system that utilizes neural network-based acoustic and language modeling techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of natural language processing (cs.CL), speech processing (cs.SD), and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper focuses on improving the state of the art on the Switchboard speech recognition task, which is a well-known benchmark in the field of speech processing. Therefore, cs.SD is the most likely category, followed by cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.SD.
